<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="189" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="189">
The male of this new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin &amp; Bao" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hitobia shaohai" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shaohai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Hitobia shaohai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yin &amp; Bao, 2012 and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. taiwanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">H. taiwanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhang, Zhu &amp; Tso, 2009 in having a short RTA and retrolaterally oriented embolus (Em), but it differs from them in the subtriangular RTA (vs beak-like in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. shaohai" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" rank="species" species="shaohai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">H. shaohai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. taiwanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">H. taiwanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the embolus with twisted apex (vs twisted apex absent in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. shaohai" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" rank="species" species="shaohai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">H. shaohai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. taiwanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">H. taiwanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (cf. Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hitobia xiaoxi sp. nov., male holotype A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D same, ventral view E same, retrolateral view F same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Co - conductor, Em - embolus, RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis, SD - sperm duct. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85655.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705985" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">4E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. SEM micrographs of Hitobia xiaoxi sp. nov., male palp (holotype) A ventral view B same, details of RTA C same, detail of embolic division D retrolateral view E same, details of RTA F same, detail of embolic division. Abbreviations: Co - conductor, Em - embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85655.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705986" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">5C-F</figureCitation>
vs 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, CM" journalOrPublisher="Hunan Science and Technology Press, Changsha" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" refId="B25" refString="Yin, CM, Peng, XJ, Yan, HM, Bao, YH, Xu, X, Tang, G, Zhou, QS, Liu, P, 2012. Fauna Hunan: Araneae in Hunan, China. Hunan Science and Technology Press, Changsha" title="Fauna Hunan: Araneae in Hunan, China." year="2012">Yin et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 631d and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, F" journalOrPublisher="Hunan Science and Technology Press, Changsha" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" refId="B26" refString="Zhang, F, Zhu, MS, Tso, IM, 2009. Three new species and two new records of Gnaphosidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Taiwan. Journal of Hebei University, Natural Science Edition 29: 528-532, 542." title="Three new species and two new records of Gnaphosidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Taiwan. Journal of Hebei University, Natural Science Edition 29: 528 - 532, 542." year="2009">Zhang et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1E, F).
</paragraph>
